node.title: FIFA releases rundown of 2023 Women's World Cup venues
node.alt: Official brand for the 2023 Women's World Cup, showing the logo, colour scheme, and indigenous designs.
node.description: Australian football fans will be able to see 35 of the 64 games in the 2023 Women's World Cup on home soil, including all of the Matildas' matches, as FIFA releases the breakdown of venues for the tournament.
node.content: ["FIFA has released the match schedule for the 2023 Women's World Cup in Australia and New Zealand.", "The tournament \u2014\u00a0which will run from July 20 to August 6, 2023 \u2014\u00a0will feature games held in nine different cities and 10 separate venues across\u00a0the two host nations.", "Of a total\u00a0of 64 games, 35 will be held in Australian venues, while 29 will be held in New Zealand.", "And the Matildas will play all their games in Australia during the tournament.", "The Women's World Cup will begin in both countries on July 20, with an opening ceremony at Eden Park in Auckland ahead of the first match with the Football Ferns.", "In Australia, the Matildas will play their opening match the same day at the new Sydney Football Stadium.", "The dates for individual games and the team\u00a0draw\u00a0will be released later."]
